subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/holdsAccount
object: Indicates an account held by this agent.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/plan
object: A .plan comment, in the tradition of finger and '.plan' files.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/givenName
object: The given name of some person.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/givenname
object: The given name of some person.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/pastProject
object: A project this person has previously worked on.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/mbox
object: A  personal mailbox, ie. an Internet mailbox associated with exactly one owner, the first owner of this mailbox. This is a 'static inverse functional property', in that  there is (across time and change) at most one individual that ever has any particular value for foaf:mbox.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/geekcode
object: A textual geekcode for this person, see http://www.geekcode.com/geek.html

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/topic_interest
object: A thing of interest to this person.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/weblog
object: A weblog of some thing (whether person, group, company etc.).

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/interest
object: A page about a topic of interest to this person.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/nick
object: A short informal nickname characterising an agent (includes login identifiers, IRC and other chat nicknames).

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/membershipClass
object: Indicates the class of individuals that are a member of a Group

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/phone
object: A phone,  specified using fully qualified tel: URI scheme (refs: http://www.w3.org/Addressing/schemes.html#tel).

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/family_name
object: The family name of some person.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/mbox_sha1sum
object: The sha1sum of the URI of an Internet mailbox associated with exactly one owner, the  first owner of the mailbox.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/firstName
object: The first name of a person.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/img
object: An image that can be used to represent some thing (ie. those depictions which are particularly representative of something, eg. one's photo on a homepage).

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/dnaChecksum
object: A checksum for the DNA of some thing. Joke.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/primaryTopic
object: The primary topic of some page or document.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/familyName
object: The family name of some person.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/birthday
object: The birthday of this Agent, represented in mm-dd string form, eg. '12-31'.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/status
object: A string expressing what the user is happy for the general public (normally) to know about their current activity.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Agent
object: An agent (eg. person, group, software or physical artifact).

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/tipjar
object: A tipjar document for this agent, describing means for payment and reward.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/mbox_sha1sum
object: sha1sum of a personal mailbox URI name

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/fundedBy
object: An organization funding a project or person.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/page
object: A page or document about this thing.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/member
object: Indicates a member of a Group

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/isPrimaryTopicOf
object: A document that this thing is the primary topic of.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/lastName
object: The last name of a person.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/schoolHomepage
object: A homepage of a school attended by the person.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/knows
object: A person known by this person (indicating some level of reciprocated interaction between the parties).

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/gender
object: The gender of this Agent (typically but not necessarily 'male' or 'female').

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/workInfoHomepage
object: A work info homepage of some person; a page about their work for some organization.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/LabelProperty
object: A foaf:LabelProperty is any RDF property with texual values that serve as labels.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/maker
object: An agent that  made this thing.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/age
object: The age in years of some agent.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/publications
object: A link to the publications of this person.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/accountName
object: Indicates the name (identifier) associated with this online account.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/currentProject
object: A current project this person works on.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/focus
object: The underlying or 'focal' entity associated with some SKOS-described concept.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Project
object: A project (a collective endeavour of some kind).

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/workplaceHomepage
object: A workplace homepage of some person; the homepage of an organization they work for.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/account
object: Indicates an account held by this agent.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/depicts
object: A thing depicted in this representation.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/
object: The Friend of a Friend (FOAF) RDF vocabulary, described using W3C RDF Schema and the Web Ontology Language.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/topic
object: A topic of some page or document.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/accountServiceHomepage
object: Indicates a homepage of the service provide for this online account.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/made
object: Something that was made by this agent.

subject: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/based_near
object: A location that something is based near, for some broadly human notion of near.
